- "Eagle that soars with the lightest fuel load" metaphorically refers to the pilot with the lowest average fuel consumption;
- "Average fuel consumption" is calculated by dividing the total fuel consumed by the number of flights for each pilot.

- "soaring the highest" refers to the longest total distance covered by the flight;
- "burning the least fuel" refers to the least amount of fuel consumed during the flight;
